DIRECTIONS\
		\uc0\u8232 Step 1.   Combine melted butter, garlic salt, white pepper, lime zest, and half of the lime juice, reserving remainder for later.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 2.   Place 2 tablespoons of water in the rear and front of a Panasonic Countertop Induction Oven grill pan. Place salmon skin-side down on the grill pan, with the thickest part of the salmon toward the center of the pan.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 3.   Brush butter mixture over salmon and slide grill pan into position. Close the oven door and press "Auto Cook." Select the fish setting, 3, and press "Start." Turn the dial to select 2 pounds and press "Start" again.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 4.   Stir remaining lime juice, mango chutney, and sriracha sauce together in a bowl.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 5.   Slide the grill pan out when there are 4 minutes remaining on the timer. Pour mango mixture evenly over the salmon. \
